			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Since the pet upgrade patch, I have noticed a dangerous and devoloping behavious in mages. Indifference. Many mages just dont seem to care anymore about their class.  Pet canni? Dismissed as a "bug fix". When even though the definition of a "bug" is totally different, here is the dfinition of "bug" from <a href="http://www.dictionary.com" target="_blank">www.dictionary.com</a>
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">   1. A defect or difficulty, as in a system or design.
<br />
   2. Computer Science. A defect in the code or routine of a program.
<br />
</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
The pet reclaim formula was not a defect or difficulty in the code of the program, so it there was nothing to fix. Only to nerf.
<br />

<br />
Second is the fix to frenzied burnout on charmed pets. This otherwise useless AA ability actually had some use. But it was nerfed, I remember people very angry over this. Funny how that anger turns to indifference over time, or over a small upgrade which does nothing for us in the long run, especially when it comes to say, mage desireability in raids.
<br />

<br />
My question to you is this. Why are we so willing to forget the horrible ways SOE has mistreated our class? Why are we so willing now that we have a VERY small upgrade, to say "If you dont like it, reroll another class!"? (Heh, I remember when NO ONE said that around here)
<br />

<br />
One frightening excuse I heard for this in chat was "We have been complaining for a long time, they have done nothing. Drop it.". Oh really? So now your just giving up? Then you dont really belong in the mage communiy me thinks.
<br />

