				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">There really is a line between defending what you feel to be correct - and accepting reality.  Want an example?  Taxes.  Want another?  Inflation.
<br />

<br />
The only real difference between who and who aren't pushovers to the system is a matter of perspective.  Some things about the mage class you gotta simply give up on unless/until SoE gives the impression that things have changed and xxx idea may be on the drawing table.  Otherwise you are going to be the "beating a dead horse" poster.
<br />

<br />
Pet Cani nerf?  yeah - I was pretty outspoken on the issue.  I even was warned to tone it down on more than one post.  Am I still outspoken about it?  No.  Why?  It's not coming back and I realize that.  Am I still gaming?  Yes - I have gotten an additional 2/tick from xpg, 3 or 5/tick from siphon series and my pets have been upgraded to the point of not being so mana starved to keep them alive during solo.  Now instead of getting 220/tick during downtime, i have been given an extra 5 or 7/tick ALL the time.  Not too shabby considering I figured the whole overall cani mana/tick was about 9/tick.  In my case, from the date of cani nerf - today, I have even more mana at my disposal overall + much better pets.  Besides, cani-nerf was not a correction of a bug, it was correction to class mana-regen balance.
<br />

<br />
Perma-FBO for charmed mobs?  Are you serious about claiming that was not a bug?  Exactly what about the "30 second duration" in the description from day one did you not understand?  Sure I know mages lost a LOT of BoT farm potential but it was a bug man.  Maybe it wouldn't have been fixed if there weren't lots of mages bragging on public forums, yelling in ooc and shout in various zones about how their pet is permanently FBO'd and doing 500+dps.  Maybe it wouldn't have been elevated to such a high priority if red server mages wasn't using this exploit to totally own BoT.  Was there even a single player in all of EQ who did NOT know about charmed mage pets being perma FBO'd?  Perhaps direct your anger at your braggard outspoken brethren - not those such as myself who silently accepted a correction of a bug.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=501504">Anthe Battlecaster</a>
